This paper is about using multilingual data for named entity recognition (NER), which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised word clusters, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The authors use discriminative NER systems, which are a type of machine learning algorithm commonly used in NLP and AI (cs.AI). Finally, the paper specifically focuses on named entities, which is a subfield of NLP and falls under the category of "Named Entities" (cs.NE).
